controls.name: ST_TITLE_DESC
controls.text: Type the text for the title bar of the wizard which you want to create.

controls.name: ST_TITLE_DESC2
controls.text:
The title for a wizard is usually in the form:
	"<verb> <noun>"

Examples:
	Upload Transactions
	Create Table

controls.name: ST_BMP_DESC
controls.text: Type the name of the bitmap entity to use.  Or, search for an existing bitmap by clicking Browse.

controls.name: ST_NEW_BMP_DESC
controls.text: To create a new bitmap of the default size (119x232 pels) with a 3D border, click the New button.

controls.name: ST_PAGECOUNT_DESC
controls.text: Type the number of wizard sheets.  Each time the user presses the Next button, they will see a different sheet.

controls.name: ST_STYLE
controls.text: &Select the style for each sheet of the wizard.

controls.name: ST_SHEET_DESC
controls.text: Use the scroll bar to select the current sheet.  Review the sheets by positioning the scroll at its leftmost position, then clicking on the scroll bar's right arrow.

controls.name: ST_DESIGN_TIPS
controls.text:
Design tips:

No event scripts are created automatically for your wizard.  Instead, there are QuickEvents on the Create and Page events of the window and on the Click event for the Back, Next, Finish, and Cancel buttons.  If you provide scripts for any of the above events, you must either use Forward_Event or Return 1, otherwise the QuickEvents won't be executed.

controls.name: ST_DESIGN_TIPS2
controls.text:
The wizard controls (like the buttons along the bottom) only display on the first sheet in the Form Designer.  They are displayed on the other sheets when the form is run.

You can select multiple controls in the Form Designer by holding down the Shift key.  You can also cut, copy, and paste controls using the Edit menu.  This is how controls can be copied or moved between different sheets.

controls.name: ST_PROGRAM_TIPS
controls.text:
Programming tips:

Use the VPosition property to get the current sheet or the total number of sheets:
	CurSheet = @@window->VPosition<1>
	SheetCount = @@window->VPosition<3>

Use the Page event to do setup processing for a sheet.  The PageAction parameter of the Page event specifies the sheet that is about to be displayed.

controls.name: ST_PROGRAM_TIPS2
controls.text:
Use the Click events on the Back, Next, and Finish buttons to perform the exit processing for a sheet.  To keep the user from moving to the next sheet, Return 0 from the Click event on the Next button.

Disable the Next or Finish buttons as a visual clue to the user that information is required.

controls.name: ST_NAME_DESC
controls.text: Type the name of the wizard which you want to create.  Or, find the name of an existing form by clicking Browse.
